0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-view","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-header","style":{"background":"#fef3c7"},"children":["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-header-inner","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"back-btn","children":"← Back to Blog"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"blog-tag","style":{"marginBottom":"1rem","display":"inline-block"},"children":"Pens & Writing"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"blog-post-title","children":"The 10 Best Gel Pens for Smooth Writing in 2026"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-meta","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":"June 18, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"·"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"6 min read"}]]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-body","children":[["$","p","p-0",{"children":"Finding a great gel pen sounds easy — there are hundreds of options. After buying and writing with over 40 different pens across three months of daily note-taking, planning, and journaling, a few clear winners emerged."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-0",{"children":"What We Tested For"}],"\n",["$","ul","ul-0",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Ink flow and consistency (no skipping or blobbing)"}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Comfort over long writing sessions"}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Dry time and smear resistance"}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Refill availability"}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":"Value per pen"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-1",{"children":"The Top Picks"}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-0",{"children":"1. Pilot G2 Fine (0.7mm)"}],"\n",["$","p","p-1",{"children":["The G2 is the benchmark. Smooth, consistent, and available everywhere. The 0.7mm tip hits the sweet spot between precision and flow. Works reliably on cheap copy paper ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"and"}]," premium dot-grid notebooks without skipping."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Best for:"}]," Everyday office use, note-taking",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Price:"}]," ~$14 for a 12-pack"]}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-1",{"children":"2. Zebra Sarasa Clip (0.5mm)"}],"\n",["$","p","p-3",{"children":"A serious contender that outperforms the G2 in one area: dry time. The Sarasa's ink dries noticeably faster, which matters for left-handed writers or anyone who smears wet ink. The retractable clip mechanism is also one of the best in this price range."}],"\n",["$","p","p-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Best for:"}]," Journaling, left-handed writers",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Price:"}]," ~$19 for a 10-pack"]}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-2",{"children":"3. Uni-ball Signo 207 (0.7mm)"}],"\n",["$","p","p-5",{"children":"If forgery-resistant ink matters to you (and for check-writing it should), the Signo 207 is built with UNI Super Ink that bonds to paper fibers. It also writes smoothly enough to use daily without feeling like a security-first compromise."}],"\n",["$","p","p-6",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Best for:"}]," Financial documents, all-purpose use",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Price:"}]," ~$10 for an 8-pack"]}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-3",{"children":"4. Pentel EnerGel RTX (0.7mm)"}],"\n",["$","p","p-7",{"children":"The EnerGel dries faster than almost any other gel pen in this roundup. Its liquid-gel hybrid ink feels closer to a rollerball — very fast, very smooth. Slightly wetter than the G2, so paper quality matters more."}],"\n",["$","p","p-8",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Best for:"}]," Fast writers, anyone who hates smearing",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Price:"}]," ~$12 for a 5-pack"]}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-2",{"children":"The Verdict"}],"\n",["$","p","p-9",{"children":["For most people, ",["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Pilot G2"}]," remains the default choice — widely available, consistent, and well-priced. If you write fast and smear easily, swap to the ","$L3"," or ","$L4",". And if you value fast-drying ink above all else, the Sarasa Clip wins."]}],"\n","$L5"]}]]}],null,"$L6"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"PUJO8GaUTtNIheOyK4Tek"}
